rposes of storing all the data in the system:","pos":[4770,4842]},{"content":"-   Network activities","pos":[4854,4876]},{"content":"-   Event activities","pos":[4882,4902]},{"content":"-   Unique entities","pos":[4908,4927]},{"content":"-   Suspicious activities","pos":[4933,4958]},{"content":"-   ATA configuration","pos":[4964,4985]},{"content":"Detectors","pos":[4988,4997]},{"content":"The Detectors use machine learning algorithms and deterministic rules to find suspicious activities and abnormal user behavior in your network.","pos":[4998,5141]},{"content":"ATA Console","pos":[5144,5155]},{"content":"The ATA Console is for configuring ATA and monitoring suspicious activities detected by ATA on your network.","pos":[5156,5264]},{"content":"The ATA Console is not dependent on the ATA Center service and will run even when the service is stopped, as long as it can communicate with the database.","pos":[5265,5419]},{"content":"Consider the following when deciding how many ATA Centers to deploy on your network:","pos":[5421,5505]},{"content":"One ATA Center can monitor a single Active Directory forest.","pos":[5511,5571]},{"content":"If you have more than one Active Directory forest you will need a minimum of one ATA Center per Active Directory forest.","pos":[5572,5692]},{"content":"In very large Active Directory deployments, a single ATA Center might not be able to handle all of the traffic of all your domain controllers.","pos":[5699,5841]},{"content":"In this case, multiple ATA Centers will be required.","pos":[5842,5894]},{"content":"The number of ATA Centers should be dictated by <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ATA capacity planning<ept id=\"p1\">](ata-capacity-planning.md)</ept>.","pos":[5895,5993],"source":" The number of ATA Centers should be dictated by [ATA capacity planning](ata-capacity-planning.md)."},{"pos":[5998,6037],"content":"ATA Gateway and ATA Lightweight Gateway","linkify":"ATA Gateway and ATA Lightweight Gateway","nodes":[{"content":"ATA Gateway and ATA L