ronizing all entities from a specific Active Directory domain proactively (similar to the mechanism used by the domain controllers themselves for replication).","pos":[8492,8707],"source":"\nThe domain synchronizer gateway is responsible for synchronizing all entities from a specific Active Directory domain proactively (similar to the mechanism used by the domain controllers themselves for replication)."},{"content":"One gateway is chosen randomly, from the list of candidates, to serve as the domain synchronizer.","pos":[8708,8805]},{"content":"If the synchronizer is offline for more than 30 minutes, another candidate is chosen instead.","pos":[8815,8908],"source":"\nIf the synchronizer is offline for more than 30 minutes, another candidate is chosen instead."},{"content":"If there is no domain synchronizer available for a specific domain, ATA will not be able to proactively synchronize entities and their changes, however ATA will reactively retrieve new entities as they are detected in the monitored traffic.","pos":[8909,9149]},{"content":"If there is no domain synchronizer available, and you search for an entity that did not have any traffic related to it, no search results will be displayed.","pos":[9155,9311]},{"content":"By default, all ATA Gateways are synchronizer candidates.","pos":[9320,9377],"source":"\nBy default, all ATA Gateways are synchronizer candidates."},{"content":"Because all ATA Lightweight Gateways are more likely to be deployed in branch sites and on small domain controllers, they are not synchronizer candidates by default.","pos":[9386,9551],"source":"\nBecause all ATA Lightweight Gateways are more likely to be deployed in branch sites and on small domain controllers, they are not synchronizer candidates by default."},{"content":"Resource limitations","pos":[9560,9580]},{"content":"The ATA Lightweight Gateway includes a monitoring component which evaluates the available compute and memory capacity on the domain controller on which it is running.","pos":[9587,9753],"source":"\nThe ATA Lightweight Gateway includes a monitoring component which evaluates the available compute and memory capacity on the domain controller on which it is running."},{"content":"The monitoring process runs every 10 seconds and dynamically updates the CPU and memory utilization quota on the ATA Lightweight Gateway process to make sure that at any given point in time, the domain controller has at least 15% of free compute and memory resources.","pos":[9754,10021]},{"content":"No matter what happens on the domain controller, this process always frees up resources to make sure the domain controller's core functionality is not affected.","pos":[10030,10190],"source":"\nNo matter what happens on the domain controller, this process always frees up resources to make sure the domain controller's core functionality is not affected."},{"content":"If this causes the ATA Lightweight Gateway to run out of resources, only partial traffic is monitored and the monitoring alert \"Dropped port mirrored network traffic\" will appear in the Health page.","pos":[10199,10397],"source":"\nIf this causes the ATA Lightweight Gateway to run out of resources, only partial traffic is monitored and the monitoring alert \"Dropped port mirrored network traffic\" will appear in the Health page."},{"content":"The following table provides an example of a domain controller with enough compute resource available to allow for a larger quota then is currently needed, so that all traffic is monitored:","pos":[10399,10588]},{"content":"Active Directory (Lsass.exe)","pos":[10610,10638]},{"content":"ATA Lightweight Gateway (Microsoft.Tri.Gateway.exe)","pos":[10639,10690]},{"content":"Miscellaneous (other processes)","pos":[10691,10722]},{"content":"ATA Lightweight Gateway Quota","pos":[10724,10753]},{"content":"Gateway dropping","pos":[10754,10770]},{"content":"30%","pos":[10773,10776]},{"content":"20%","pos":[10777,10780]},{"content":"10%","pos":[10781,10784]},{"content